# ClaimStation Project (App Only)

**App-only**: This rule applies only when working in the ClaimStation app (`claimstation-app`). Ignore it when working in claimstation-www or other directories.

A web app for tracking reimbursement claims (health insurance, work expenses, government subsidies).

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: Next.js 14+ (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, shadcn/ui
- **Backend**: Supabase (PostgreSQL, Auth, Storage, Edge Functions)
- **Hosting**: Vercel (frontend), Supabase (backend)
- **AI**: OpenAI API (optional, user-enabled)

## Key Directories

- `claimstation-app/src/app/` — Next.js App Router pages
- `claimstation-app/src/components/`, `src/components/ui/` — React and shadcn/ui components
- `claimstation-app/src/lib/` — Utilities, Supabase client
- `claimstation-app/src/types/` — TypeScript types
- `claimstation-app/src/api/` — API route handlers
- `claimstation-app/supabase/migrations/`, `supabase/functions/` — DB migrations, Edge Functions

## Core Entities

Claims, Transactions, Bank Accounts, Categories, Reimbursing Entities.

